    • Method Detail

      • execute

        public void execute​(LibraryData data)
        Execute the ADD command, this adds the book entries from the given files. The file path is expected to be loaded before execution. If invalid path is given or the file is not formatted well, error message will be displayed to console. If error is encountered during execution, the library will not be changed.
        Specified by:
        execute in class LibraryCommand
        Parameters:
        data - book data to be considered for command execution.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - library data is null or file path is null

      • parseArguments

        protected boolean parseArguments​(java.lang.String argumentInput)
        Check whether the file path has the allowed file extension. Note this method will not check the validity of the file path. Currently, only one extension ".csv" is supported. If you want to allow more extensions please add them to AllowedFileExtension enum.
        Overrides:
        parseArguments in class LibraryCommand
        Parameters:
        argumentInput - argument input for this command
        Returns:
        true if argument ends with supported file extension, false otherwise
